g.ns9:text: Spin polarization = difference in population between $\\ket{0}$ and $\\ket{\\pm 1}$

When reaching a critical ($\sim$ 1 ppm) NV density :

$\bullet$ Lifetimes get shorter

$\bullet$ Polarization profile get non-exponential

Dipole-dipole coupling $J \approx 30$ kHz for [NV]=3 ppm

$\to J > 1/T_1$ 

Depolarization slower than the flip-flop rate
